<section id="mission">
    <h2>Mission Statement</h2>
    <p>To create, culminate, and collaborate on all forms of science and technology, driving the betterment and evolution of humanity.</p>
</section>

<section id="vision-values">
    <h2>Vision & Values</h2>
    <p><br>A Better Baseline envisions a future where technology and humanity evolve in harmony, powered by community-driven innovation, individual responsibility, and radical kindness.</p><br>
 
<br><p>1.Tolerance Paradox  
We embrace diverse thoughts, cultures, and identities while firmly rejecting manipulation, harm, or oppression. Peace is our goal, but we stand firm in defending these ideals when necessary.</p><br>  

<br><p>2.Harm-Conscious Dynamic
We prioritize the well-being of people and the planet over power and profit, promoting awareness of the ripple effects our actions create.</p><br>

<br><p>3.Apolitical & Areligious
We focus on shared human values, cooperation, and the pursuit of knowledge—free from political and religious distractions.

*We welcome individuals of all beliefs but choose not to be solely guided by them in our mission.</p><br>

<p><br>4. Harmony with the Planet  
We advocate for sustainable living and accurate information to foster a relationship with Earth that enriches both humanity and the natural world.</p><br>

<p>5. Child-Centric Approach
We prioritize children’s well-being and development through evidence-based principles in a deeply loving environment, ensuring they thrive and shape a better future.</p>
</section>

<section id="projects">
    <h2>Core Projects:</h2>
    <p>
         The Homestead Project;<br>
        A living lab—self-sustaining, off-grid, and designed to test and refine technologies in energy, agriculture, construction, and community design. The Homestead’s goal is to achieve a net-zero carbon footprint at launch, with rapid progression into net-positive housing—generating more energy, clean water, and resources than it consumes. Ultimately, the project serves as a blueprint for a repeatable, attainable way of living—one that can be adapted by communities worldwide to create a sustainable future for generations to come.
    </p><br>

    <p>
         Frequency Research;<br>
        A deep dive into how frequency, resonance, and vibration influence both technology and life itself. This project will also maintain a Frequency Database — an open and ever-evolving log that catalogs the frequencies of objects, materials, biological beings, and natural phenomena. This database serves both scientific exploration and practical application, from healing technologies to material manipulation.
    </p><br>

    <p>
        Baseline Technologies;<br>
        Open-source tools, systems, and platforms designed to empower individuals and communities to contribute to scientific and technological progress — accessible, adaptable, and ethically created.
    </p><br>

    <p>
        The Tolerance Paradox Initiative;<br>
        A cultural technology project — defining and promoting spaces where intellectual freedom thrives without sacrificing the baseline requirement of human dignity and respect.
    </p>
</section>

